sql:
SELECT customer_id
FROM customers
WHERE loyalty_points > (SELECT AVG(loyalty_points) FROM customers);

SELECT amount, tip
FROM amounts
ORDER BY amount DESC;

external_knowledge:
- 'First quarter of 2023' refers to the period from January 1, 2023, to March 31, 2023;
- 'Exceeded a value of $20' means the total cost of the order is greater than $20;
- 'At least one entree' means the order includes at least one menu item from the 'entree' category.

- "showered the most gold" refers to the highest total spend;
- "loyal patrons" refers to customers who have made multiple orders;
- "tale of their visits" includes the number of orders, average rating, and number of promotions used;
- "ranking them from the most generous to the least" means ordering by total spend in descending order.

- "top three most costly dining excursions" refers to the three most expensive orders for each customer;
- "paid for with plastic" refers to orders paid by credit card;
- "delivered by the hand of John Smith" refers to deliveries made by a specific delivery personnel named John Smith.

- 'Patrons who have indulged the most' refers to customers with the highest total order value;
- 'Swiftness of the kitchens' refers to the average delivery time for the restaurants;
- 'Magical offers' refers to the promotions;
- 'Bloom' refers to the total revenue generated by the promotions.

- "shining stars in the culinary world" refers to restaurants with an average rating greater than 4.0;
- "earning high praise from diners" refers to the average rating of the restaurant;
- "offering at least one dish that's worth the extra coin" refers to having at least one menu item priced over $10.00.

- "Frequent customers" refers to customers who have placed multiple orders.;
- "Highest average order total" is determined by the average cost of orders across all orders for each restaurant.;
- The results are sorted by the average order total in descending order, and then by the restaurant name in ascending order.

- 'completed their journey from placement to delivery' refers to orders with a status of 'delivered';
- 'the year 2023' refers to the period between January 1, 2023, and December 31, 2023;
- 'the delivery confirmation came after the order was placed' refers to the condition that the status update date is after the order date.

- 'Most loyal customer' refers to the customer with the highest total loyalty points;
- 'Dined at Italian restaurants' means the customer has placed orders at restaurants with the cuisine type 'Italian';
- 'Stellar reputation' means the restaurant has an average rating greater than 4.0.

- 'Generous patrons' refers to customers who have spent more than $50 in total;
- 'Favorite gourmet havens' refers to restaurants with an average rating greater than 4.0;
- 'Lavish feasts' refers to the total amount of the orders;
- 'Reputation shines brighter than a 4-star review' means the average rating of the restaurant is greater than 4.0.

- 'blossomed into deliveries' refers to orders that have the status 'delivered';
- 'seeds of success sown by both successful payments' refers to payments with the status 'paid';
- 'presence of a promotional offer' refers to orders with a non-zero `promotion_id`.

- 'top 3 most acclaimed orders' refers to the orders with the highest ratings;
- 'dining establishment' refers to the restaurant;
- 'patrons' refers to customers.
